the oldest classical british and latin writings had little or no space between words and could be boustrophedon alternating directions. over time, text direction left to right becane standardized. word dividers and terminal punctuation become common. the first way divide sentences into groups was the original paragraphos, similar to an underscore at the beginning of the new group the greek paragrahos evolved into the pilcrow which in english manuscripts in the middle ages canseen inserted inline between sentences.
